  "prompt": "What does \"natural causality\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Natural causality\" refers to the principle that events in the natural world are caused by prior physical events or natural processes, following consistent and observable laws of nature, without supernatural or mystical intervention. In other words, it suggests that everything that happens has a rational, scientific explanation based on physical cause and effect relationships. This concept is fundamental to scientific thinking and empirical approaches to understanding the world, emphasizing that natural phenomena can be explained through observable, measurable interactions between physical entities.",
